Introduction

Hey guys, I’m Mathmagician10. I am an amateur caster who is looking to use my statistics degree for more than just my day job, so I created this team analysis in R with what feels like a million datasets from DatDota. HUGE thanks to Noxville, Bonk, and TinT for allowing this stats sheet to happen cause without DatDota allowing nice API, Bonk’s ideas and TinT’s support this would not be possible. I hope you guys enjoy what you read. I’m hoping this makes the draft stage a little more fun for you guys to watch since you could have a better idea of what is coming. I’ll take any and all suggestions/criticisms as I would love to know what I can do to be better. For today’s analysis, we have the BTS Pro Series AM Series 9

Team Statistics BTS Pro Series AM Season 9

The following data will be for all phases of the draft. The goal will be to determine what the expected picks and bans will be solely based off of statistics, not necessarily previous games or previous pick/bans. Inherently, this makes the first phase draft data the most impactful as you will likely dedicate one of your first bans to taking away high priority heroes on the other team. Typically these are not in reaction to the other bans you would have already seen.
